text.section:
The governing body of Garrett County and of a municipal corporation in Garrett County shall grant a property tax credit under this section against the county and municipal corporation property tax imposed on:
property that is:
owned by the Maryland Ornithological Society, Incorporated; and
known as the Carey Run Sanctuary;
property that is:
owned by the Swanton Community Center, Incorporated;
known as the Swanton Community Center; and
used only for community, civic, or educational purposes;
property that is:
owned by the Crellin Community Center, Incorporated;
known as the Crellin Community Center; and
used only for community, civic, or educational purposes;
property that is:
owned by the Bittinger Community Center, Incorporated;
known as the Bittinger Community Center; and
used only for community, civic, or educational purposes; and
property that is:
owned by the Garrett County Agricultural Fair Association, Incorporated; and
used only for the purposes of the Association.

section.section:
In authorizing a credit under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, the governing body of the county may:
set the amount and duration of the tax credit;
provide for additional eligibility criteria for the tax credit;
provide for regulations and procedures for the administration of requests for the tax credit; and
adopt any other provision necessary to administer the credit.
